\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure that a postmortem review is initiated for every cybersecurity incident declared under Chapter 4 authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall assign the Postmortem Lead in accordance with the separation of duties requirements defined in Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as Postmortem Lead when the Incident Commander for the incident was not the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as a mandatory participant in the postmortem meeting when the Assistant IT Director serves as Postmortem Lead.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review and approve the completed internal postmortem report.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review and approve the external (redacted) postmortem derivative prior to distribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall route postmortem findings to the appropriate remediation and improvement pipelines in accordance with Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall determine whether operational findings from the postmortem warrant opening a 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Problem Management Policy) Problem record,
 in accordance with the jurisdictional boundary established in Section 6.7.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure that the Incident Commander for the reviewed incident —
 the IT Director or designee as designated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Incident Response Policy Overview) —
 participates in the postmortem meeting as a mandatory attendee.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure that the Incident Commander provides the Postmortem Lead with a written summary of key response decisions,
 rationale,
 and observations prior to or during the postmortem meeting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall retain postmortem report approval,
 exception authorization under Section 4,
 and findings routing disposition under Section 6.6 as non-transferable IT Director functions that shall not pass to a designee serving as Incident Commander.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize formal exceptions to this policy in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as Postmortem Lead when the Incident Commander for the incident was the IT Director,
 in accordance with Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall compile the communication data package prepared under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Communication Protocols and Partner Integration) and shall ensure its inclusion in the internal postmortem report.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall compile all source documentation from the incident work order,
 Chapter 4 checklist,
 and related records in preparation for the postmortem meeting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall prepare the external (redacted) postmortem derivative in accordance with Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall preserve the Postmortem Lead's draft findings as a permanent attachment to the postmortem record in accordance with Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain postmortem records in the System of Engagement in accordance with Section 6.8.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall attend the postmortem meeting unless excused by the Postmortem Lead.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall provide factual input regarding response actions taken,
 observations made,
 and difficulties encountered during the incident.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations Department personnel involved in or supporting cybersecurity incident response.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Adherence to postmortem initiation,
 completion timelines,
 report content requirements,
 findings routing obligations,
 and retention requirements shall be assessed through the internal audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The following conditions constitute specific non-compliance with this policy.
 Non-compliance may result in corrective action in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to initiate a postmortem review for a declared cybersecurity incident.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to complete the internal postmortem report within the timeline established in Section 6.3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to preserve the Postmortem Lead's draft findings as required by Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to prepare the external postmortem derivative within the timeline established in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to route actionable findings in accordance with Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Failure to maintain postmortem records in accordance with Section 6.8.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy require written approval from the IT Director in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No open-ended exceptions are permitted.
 All approved exceptions shall be documented and time-bounded.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 The following obligations constitute a non-waivable floor and shall not be reduced or eliminated by any approved exception:
 the mandatory postmortem trigger (Section 6.1),
 the separation of duties requirement (Section 6.2),
 the draft findings preservation requirement (Section 6.4),
 and the retention obligations (Section 6.8).
 No exception may permit the Incident Commander for an incident to serve as Postmortem Lead for that same incident.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

