\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Internal postmortem reports,
 external postmortem derivatives,
 draft findings attachments,
 postmortem meeting attendance records,
 and all supporting documentation produced under this policy shall be retained in the System of Engagement for a minimum of three (3) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the Operational Handback was declared,
 in accordance with NRS 239.125 and the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule:
 LRDA 20071728 (IT Security Audit Records).
 Where multiple retention requirements apply,
 the longest applicable period shall govern.
 The IT Director shall ensure that postmortem records are not disposed of during any active litigation hold,
 public records preservation requirement,
 audit,
 or other legal hold event.
\end_layout

